                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.6363/453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cox</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-29T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 29, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>179. My 177, August 28, 5 p.m. Standard Oil Co. today tells me it has just signed
                    temporary agreement together with Shell-Mex which does not obligate companies to
                    accept marketing arrangement. Commission informs oil companies that final date
                    for their acceptance of the latter is September 22.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cox</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
